      "## Step 8 — Common RAG Pitfalls and Mitigations\n",
      "\n",
      "### 1. **Hallucination** — Claude invents an answer not in the context\n",
      "**Mitigation:** Explicitly tell Claude to decline out-of-scope questions (as we did in the system prompt).\n",
      "\n",
      "### 2. **Irrelevant Context** — similarity search returns chunks that don't match the intent\n",
      "**Mitigation:** Improve chunking (semantic boundaries), increase embedding quality, or use a hybrid search (semantic + keyword).\n",
      "\n",
      "### 3. **Too Much Context** — many chunks dilute signal\n",
      "**Mitigation:** Retrieve fewer chunks, or re-rank results with a second-pass filter.\n",
      "\n",
      "### 4. **Missing Information** — the knowledge base doesn't have the answer\n",
      "**Mitigation:** Ensure your knowledge base is comprehensive; log misses and augment over time.\n",
      "\n",
      "### 5. **Stale Context** — outdated docs\n",
      "**Mitigation:** Version your docs, refresh embeddings when docs change, track which chunks are used.\n",
      "\n",
      "Let's test a question where the answer is NOT in our docs:"
    ]
  },
  {
    "cell_type": "code",
    "execution_count": null,
    "metadata": {},
    "outputs": [],
    "source": [
      "out_of_scope = \"What's the weather today?\"\n",
      "result = rag_answer(out_of_scope, chunks)\n",
      "print(f\"Q: {out_of_scope}\")\n",
      "print(f\"\\nA: {result['answer']}\")"
    ]
  },
  {
    "cell_type": "markdown",
